{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25"]]},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"Evaluate your app for Accessibility Nutrition Labels","role":"sampleCode","roleHeading":"WWDC25"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-224-evaluate-your-app-for-accessibility-nutrition-labels"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-224-Evaluate-your-app-for-Accessibility-Nutrition-Labels","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Use Accessibility Nutrition Labels on your App Store product page to highlight the accessibility features supported by your app. You’ll learn how to evaluate your app’s accessibility features — such as VoiceOver, Larger Text, Captions, and more — and choose accurate and informative Accessibility Nutrition Labels. You’ll also find out how to approach accessibility throughout the design phase.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (24 min)","type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/224"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Related-Sessions","text":"Related Sessions","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC24-10074-Get-started-with-Dynamic-Type"],"style":"list","type":"links"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"WWDC25-Icon.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25","title":"WWDC25","role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC25.jpg"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 26, Swift 6.2, iOS\/macOS\/tvOS\/visionOS 26."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Foundation Models"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AlarmKit"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PermissionKit"},{"type":"text","text":", and more."}],"type":"topic","kind":"article"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC24-10074-Get-started-with-Dynamic-Type":{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Dynamic Type lets people choose their preferred text size across the system and all of their apps. To help you get started supporting Dynamic Type, we’ll cover the fundamentals: How it works, how to find issues with scaling text in your app, and how to take practical steps using SwiftUI and UIKit to create a great Dynamic Type experience. We’ll also show how you can best use the Large Content Viewer to make navigation controls accessible to everyone.","type":"text"}],"title":"Get started with Dynamic Type","role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc24-10074-get-started-with-dynamic-type","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC24-10074-Get-started-with-Dynamic-Type"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"identifier":"do